name: adexchangeseller
title: Ad Exchange Seller API
description: Accesses the inventory of Ad Exchange seller users and generates reports.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

fields.name: rows
fields.desc: The output rows of the report. Each row is a list of cells; one for each dimension in the request, followed by one for each metric in the request. The dimension cells contain strings, and the metric cells contain numbers.

fields.name: totalMatchedRows
fields.desc: The total number of rows matched by the report request. Fewer rows may be returned in the response due to being limited by the row count requested or the report row limit.

fields.name: totals
fields.desc: The totals of the report. This is the same length as any other row in the report; cells corresponding to dimension columns are empty.

fields.name: warnings
fields.desc: Any warnings associated with generation of the report.

fields.name: averages
fields.desc: The averages of the report. This is the same length as any other row in the report; cells corresponding to dimension columns are empty.

fields.name: headers
fields.desc: The header information of the columns requested in the report. This is a list of headers; one for each dimension in the request, followed by one for each metric in the request.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the header.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of the header; one of DIMENSION, METRIC_TALLY, METRIC_RATIO, or METRIC_CURRENCY.

fields.name: currency
fields.desc: The currency of this column. Only present if the header type is METRIC_CURRENCY.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind this is, in this case adexchangeseller#report.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this reporting metadata entry, corresponding to the name of the appropriate dimension or metric.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adexchangeseller#reportingMetadataEntry.

fields.name: requiredDimensions
fields.desc: The names of the dimensions which the dimension or metric this reporting metadata entry describes requires to also be present in order for the report to be valid. Omitting these will not cause an error or warning, but may result in data which cannot be correctly interpreted.

fields.name: requiredMetrics
fields.desc: The names of the metrics which the dimension or metric this reporting metadata entry describes requires to also be present in order for the report to be valid. Omitting these will not cause an error or warning, but may result in data which cannot be correctly interpreted.

fields.name: supportedProducts
fields.desc: The codes of the projects supported by the dimension or metric this reporting metadata entry describes.

fields.name: compatibleDimensions
fields.desc: For metrics this is a list of dimension IDs which the metric is compatible with, for dimensions it is a list of compatibility groups the dimension belongs to.

fields.name: compatibleMetrics
fields.desc: The names of the metrics the dimension or metric this reporting metadata entry describes is compatible with.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: The locations in which ads appear. (Only valid for content and mobile content ads). Acceptable values for content ads are: TOP_LEFT, TOP_CENTER, TOP_RIGHT, MIDDLE_LEFT, MIDDLE_CENTER, MIDDLE_RIGHT, BOTTOM_LEFT, BOTTOM_CENTER, BOTTOM_RIGHT, MULTIPLE_LOCATIONS. Acceptable values for mobile content ads are: TOP, MIDDLE, BOTTOM, MULTIPLE_LOCATIONS.

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: Time when this deal stops being active in seconds since the epoch (GMT). If not set then this deal is valid until manually disabled by the publisher.

fields.name: fixedCpm
fields.desc: The fixed price for this preferred deal. In cpm micros of currency according to currencyCode. If set, then this preferred deal is eligible for the fixed price tier of buying (highest priority, pay exactly the configured fixed price).

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Unique identifier of this preferred deal.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Kind of resource this is, in this case adexchangeseller#preferredDeal.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: Time when this deal becomes active in seconds since the epoch (GMT). If not set then this deal is active immediately upon creation.

fields.name: advertiserName
fields.desc: The name of the advertiser this deal is for.

fields.name: buyerNetworkName
fields.desc: The name of the buyer network this deal is for.

fields.name: currencyCode
fields.desc: The currency code that applies to the fixed_cpm value. If not set then assumed to be USD.

methods.name: generate
methods.desc: Generate an Ad Exchange report based on the report request sent in the query parameters. Returns the result as JSON; to retrieve output in CSV format specify "alt=csv" as a query parameter.

pathParams.name: accountId
pathParams.desc: Account which owns the generated report.

requiredQueryParams.name: startDate
requiredQueryParams.desc: Start of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.

requiredQueryParams.name: endDate
requiredQueryParams.desc: End of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.

optinalQueryParams.name: metric
optinalQueryParams.desc: Numeric columns to include in the report.

optinalQueryParams.name: startIndex
optinalQueryParams.desc: Index of the first row of report data to return.

optinalQueryParams.name: locale
optinalQueryParams.desc: Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local language. Defaults to "en_US" if not specified.

optinalQueryParams.name: sort
optinalQueryParams.desc: The name of a dimension or metric to sort the resulting report on, optionally prefixed with "+" to sort ascending or "-" to sort descending. If no prefix is specified, the column is sorted ascending.

optinalQueryParams.name: dimension
optinalQueryParams.desc: Dimensions to base the report on.

optinalQueryParams.name: filter
optinalQueryParams.desc: Filters to be run on the report.

optinalQueryParams.name: maxResults
optinalQueryParams.desc: The maximum number of rows of report data to return.
